{
  "texts": [
    "Each discriminator specializes in a specific class and possesses in-depth knowledge of the unique features of that class.",
    "Consequently, the classification result becomes more accurate, and the model is more reliable under clinical scenarios where data variability can be very high.",
    "Due to the discriminators, they can focus on class-specific attributes.",
    "Therefore, the model learns to generate realistic images while most effectively distinguishing between different kinds of nodules.The DDDG-GAN features a sophisticated mechanism of feature fusion.",
    "It fuses the discriminative feature maps output by the dual generators and dual discriminators into an attentive feature map."
  ]
}